						<summary>

						<p>On the north, east and south bases of the central shrine in the Kāḷahastīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājēndra I. Year 22: 1043-44 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription contains a portion of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti Tirumaṉṉi vaḷara</hi> etc., of the king.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift for a perpetual lamp. The name of the donor is lost. It mentions Mummuḍiśōḻapuram, a township in Perumbāṇappāḍi Āṟṟūr-nāḍu in Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa-maṇḍalam and Niṉṟai in Niṉṟaiyil-nāḍu. The measure <hi rend="italic">Arumoḻidēvan</hi> is also mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
